  "text": "Yet, there were also framings of 'community' as an entity with potential to influence the success (or otherwise) of a venture, with money mediating relationships between the 'community' and external entities, to generate 'acceptance' of a development, for example a nuclear energy facility [CITATION_1] 13 \"The local population's consent was obtained via negotiations where the prime stake concerned the financial compensation of the host and neighbouring settlements.\" (Vari & Ferencz, 2007, p189) .",
